p.-text Chi has adopted a subset of icons from Cyclops and CenturyLink's Cloud Application Manager.

h3 Using Icons
p.-text Icons can be added via SVG or Web Font. Choose the method that best suits your projects needs.

h4 SVG & JS Method
p.-text SVG based implementations provide better semantics, accessibility, rendering, and reliability. Place the following script in your projects footer to use this method.
.-mb2
  :code(lang='html')
    <script src="https://assets.ctl.io/chi/0.8.2/chi-icons.js"></script>
p.-text Then to render an SVG icon, apply the class <code>a-icon</code> to an element as well as the icon specific class name from the <a href="#available-icons">Available Icons</a> list.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-icon.icon-logo-centurylink
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-century-link"></div>

h4 Web Font & CSS Method
p.-text Web Font based implementations offer the widest browser support, fastest rendering speed, and require no additional script or stylesheet.
p.-text To render a Web Font icon, apply the class <code>a-icon</code> to an <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> tag and specify the name of the icon you wish to use in the <code>&lt;i&gt;</code>'s class attribute:
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    i(class='a-icon icon-logo-centurylink')
  :code(lang="html")
    <i class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink"></i>

h3 Sizes
p.-text By default, icons render at 16x16px (<code>-sm</code>). Apply size classes to render icons larger or smaller:
  | <code>-xs</code>, <code>-sm</code>, <code>-md</code>, <code>-lg</code>, <code>-xl</code>, <code>-xxl</code>.
p.-text Two alternate small classes are available for specific app scenarios. Use <code>-sm2</code>
  | for displaying 20px icons within a 40px container (e.g. large button), and <code>-sm3</code> for displaying
  | 24px icons within a 48px container.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-grid.-align-items--end
      each size in ['xs', 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl', 'xxl']
        div.-p2
          div(class=`a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -${size}`)
  :code(lang="html")
    <!-- -xs : 12x12px -->
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -xs"></div>
    <!-- -sm : 16x16px -->
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -sm"></div>
    <!-- -md : 32x32px -->
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md"></div>
    <!-- -lg : 64x64px -->
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -lg"></div>
    <!-- -xl : 96x96px -->
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -xl"></div>
    <!-- -xxl : 128x128px -->
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -xxl"></div>

h3 Colors
p.-text By default, icons are the same color as text. Use Chi text color utilities to set a specific color.
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .a-grid.-align-items--end
      each color in ['Base', 'Brand', 'Success', 'Warning', 'Danger', 'Info', 'Inverse', 'Muted']
        div.-p2
          div(class=`a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -text${color}`)
  :code(lang="html")
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textBrand"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textSuccess"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textWarning"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textDanger"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textInfo"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textInverse"></div>
    <div class="a-icon icon-logo-centurylink -md -textMuted"></div>

